result.name: The Jockey Club Kau Sai Chau Public Golf Course

reviews.text: Absolutely cracking public golf course. East is very challenging course, south a little more forgiving. Both are gorgeous.  North course is also a beauty, but walking only... However renting a battery powered trolley is very cheap for your clubs.  The restaurant is more of a canteen.. It could do with a little more refinement.

East Course the Best , but many challenges.
if over 18 handicap use north or south course to minimize the damage to your golf ball stocks.😉
The island’s nature is beautiful and the facilities are perfect. After a shower, you can have a drink in the restaurant, perfect.
Very nice and challenging South Course. There are 2 more courses. One of the cheaper golf options in HK. You need a handicap card or need at least one person with one to play.
Not for summer games, not enough shade. But scenery is just superb

reviews.text: Good for a quick bite after golfing. Staff is helpful. The scenery is good. They only have buffet and food quality is below average, and variety of food is limited for a buffet. The costs of buffet covers your ferry ticket if go there after 16.00 on weekends.
Wonderful to have a public golf club in hk such a small city. The tee, the driveway, and the green are well kept. The food from the restaurant was average though
Surrounded by the golf courses, scenic view. Many choices other than buffet.
Food are ok.  Service was not that good.  Overall is convenient, no need to carry the golf club around.
peaceful n reasonable price
